    <h1 class="western"><strong>SERVICE LEVEL AGREEMENT (SLA)</strong></h1>
<p><strong>TECHIESpirals (Pty) Ltd</strong></p>
<p><strong>Effective Date:</strong> [Insert date]</p>
<p>This Service Level Agreement (“SLA”) sets out the service
availability, support commitments, and service credits applicable to
the SaaS Services provided by <strong>TECHIESpirals (Pty) Ltd</strong>
(“TECHIESpirals”, “we”, “us”).</p>
<p>This SLA forms part of, and is subject to, the SaaS Terms of
Service or Subscription Agreement entered into between TECHIESpirals
and the Customer.</p>
<hr/>

<h2 class="western">1. Definitions</h2>
<ul>
	<li><p><strong>“Business Hours”</strong> means 08:00–17:00
	South African Standard Time (SAST), Monday to Friday, excluding
	public holidays.</p></li>
	<li><p><strong>“Downtime”</strong> means the SaaS Services are
	unavailable to all users, excluding Permitted Downtime.</p></li>
	<li><p><strong>“Monthly Uptime Percentage”</strong> means:</p>
	<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm">&nbsp;minutes&nbsp;in&nbsp;month&nbsp;–&nbsp;Downtime&nbsp;minutes&nbsp;in&nbsp;monthTotal&nbsp;minutes&nbsp;in&nbsp;monthTotal&nbsp;minutes&nbsp;in&nbsp;month&nbsp;–&nbsp;Downtime​×100
		</p></li>
	<li><p><strong>“Permitted Downtime”</strong> means scheduled
	maintenance and events excluded under Section 6.</p></li>
	<li><p><strong>“Severity Level”</strong> means the
	classification of an incident as defined in Section 4.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr/>

<h2 class="western">2. Service Availability Commitment</h2>
<p>TECHIESpirals commits to a <strong>Monthly Uptime Percentage of
99.5%</strong> for the SaaS Services.</p>
<p>Availability is measured on a per-calendar-month basis.</p>
<hr/>

<h2 class="western">3. Monitoring and Measurement</h2>
<ul>
	<li><p>Availability is monitored using internal and third-party
	monitoring tools.</p></li>
	<li><p>Uptime calculations are based on TECHIESpirals’ monitoring
	data, which will be the authoritative source.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr/>

<h2 class="western">4. Incident Severity Levels and Response Times</h2>
<h3 class="western"><strong>Severity 1 – Critical</strong></h3>
<ul>
	<li><p><strong>Description:</strong> Complete service outage or
	critical business impact</p></li>
	<li><p><strong>Initial Response Time:</strong> 1 hour</p></li>
	<li><p><strong>Target Resolution:</strong> 8 hours</p></li>
	<li><p><strong>Support Coverage:</strong> 24/7</p></li>
</ul>
<hr/>

<h3 class="western"><strong>Severity 2 – High</strong></h3>
<ul>
	<li><p><strong>Description:</strong> Major functionality impaired,
	no reasonable workaround</p></li>
	<li><p><strong>Initial Response Time:</strong> 4 business hours</p></li>
	<li><p><strong>Target Resolution:</strong> 2 business days</p></li>
	<li><p><strong>Support Coverage:</strong> Business Hours</p></li>
</ul>
<hr/>

<h3 class="western"><strong>Severity 3 – Medium</strong></h3>
<ul>
	<li><p><strong>Description:</strong> Partial functionality issue
	with workaround available</p></li>
	<li><p><strong>Initial Response Time:</strong> 1 business day</p></li>
	<li><p><strong>Target Resolution:</strong> 5 business days</p></li>
	<li><p><strong>Support Coverage:</strong> Business Hours</p></li>
</ul>
<hr/>

<h3 class="western"><strong>Severity 4 – Low</strong></h3>
<ul>
	<li><p><strong>Description:</strong> Minor issue, cosmetic bug, or
	general enquiry</p></li>
	<li><p><strong>Initial Response Time:</strong> 2 business days</p></li>
	<li><p><strong>Target Resolution:</strong> Best effort</p></li>
	<li><p><strong>Support Coverage:</strong> Business Hours</p></li>
</ul>
<hr/>

<h2 class="western">5. Support Channels</h2>
<p>Support requests may be submitted via:</p>
<ul>
	<li><p>Email: [insert support email]</p></li>
	<li><p>Ticketing system or portal (where applicable)</p></li>
</ul>
<p>Emergency escalation procedures may be provided separately to
enterprise customers.</p>
<hr/>

<h2 class="western">6. Scheduled Maintenance and Exclusions</h2>
<p>6.1 <strong>Scheduled Maintenance</strong></p>
<ul>
	<li><p>May be performed outside Business Hours where possible</p></li>
	<li><p>Will be communicated at least <strong>48 hours in advance</strong></p></li>
	<li><p>Does not count as Downtime</p></li>
</ul>
<p>6.2 <strong>Exclusions</strong><br/>
Downtime does <strong>not</strong>
include unavailability caused by:</p>
<ul>
	<li><p>Force majeure events</p></li>
	<li><p>Customer systems, networks, or internet connectivity</p></li>
	<li><p>Third-party services or integrations not controlled by
	TECHIESpirals</p></li>
	<li><p>Customer misuse or breach of the Terms</p></li>
	<li><p>Emergency security patches</p></li>
</ul>
<hr/>

<h2 class="western">7. Service Credits</h2>
<p>7.1 If TECHIESpirals fails to meet the Monthly Uptime Percentage,
the Customer may be eligible for <strong>service credits</strong> as
set out below:</p>
