<p>7.2 Service credits:</p>
<ul>
	<li><p>Are the Customer’s <strong>sole and exclusive remedy</strong>
	for availability failures</p></li>
	<li><p>Are applied to future invoices</p></li>
	<li><p>Must be claimed within <strong>30 days</strong> of the
	relevant month</p></li>
</ul>
<hr/>

<h2 class="western">8. Customer Responsibilities</h2>
<p>The Customer is responsible for:</p>
<ul>
	<li><p>Ensuring its users are trained and authorised</p></li>
	<li><p>Maintaining secure credentials</p></li>
	<li><p>Promptly reporting incidents with sufficient detail</p></li>
	<li><p>Implementing reasonable internal security controls</p></li>
</ul>
<p>Failure to meet these responsibilities may affect service levels.</p>
<hr/>

<h2 class="western">9. Data Backup and Recovery</h2>
<ul>
	<li><p>TECHIESpirals performs regular backups of production systems
	in accordance with internal policies.</p></li>
	<li><p>Backup frequency and retention periods may vary by service
	tier.</p></li>
	<li><p>Disaster recovery objectives (RPO/RTO) may be agreed
	separately for enterprise customers.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr/>

<h2 class="western">10. SLA Review and Changes</h2>
<p>TECHIESpirals may update this SLA from time to time.<br/>
Material
changes will be communicated in advance and will not reduce service
levels for the current subscription term without Customer consent.</p>
<hr/>

<h2 class="western">11. Relationship to Agreement</h2>
<p>In the event of a conflict between this SLA and the SaaS Terms of
Service or Subscription Agreement, the <strong>Subscription Agreement
shall prevail</strong>, unless expressly stated otherwise.</p>
<hr/>

